FBIS4-29349 "dreas117_a_94017" FBIS-EAS-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Former Envoy Foresees No Accord on UN Seat Former Envoy Foresees No Accord on UN Seat OW1606130394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1256 GMT 16 Jun 94 OW1606130394 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, June 16 KYODO -- The United Nations will not be able to revise its charter before 1996 to allow Japan to become a permanent member of its security council, former Japanese ambassador to the UN Yoshio Hatano predicted Thursday [16 June]. Hatano also said in a speech that a midterm report on UN reform by a working committee, due this fall, will not detail an increase in the number of UN Security Council members. He said it would be impossible for the 184-nation working panel to produce an agreement.
